<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Players International.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Players International.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Salomon Brothers said it downgraded Players International Inc to hold from buy.</p>
<p>-- The stock closed at 6-14/16 Tuesday.</p>
<p>-- Salomon cited &quot;July jurisdictional results for both Illinois and Louisiana as well as margin pressure at the company's Lake Charles, La., and Metropolis, Ill., properties.&quot;  </p>
<p>-- Salomon's gaming analyst Bruce Turner also lowered his earnings estimates for the company, to $0.35 per share from $0.80 for 1996, to $0.45 from $1.15 for 1997, and to $0.55 from $1.25 for 1998.</p>
<p>-- The pared earnings outlook is based on &quot;increased competitive pressures in the Lake Charles and Metropolis gaming markets.&quot;</p>
</text>
